{{Use British English|date=September 2014}} {{Infobox organization |name = Cambridge Assessment International Education |image = |caption = |motto = Learn, Discover, Achieve |formation = 1858<ref>{{cite web|title=Cambridge Assessment – Heritage|url=http://www.cambridgeassessment.org.uk/about-us/who-we-are/our-heritage/}}</ref> |parent_organisation = [[Cambridge Assessment]] |website = {{URL|https://www.cambridgeinternational.org}} |formerly = (University of) '''C'''ambridge '''I'''nternational '''E'''xaminations }}
'''Cambridge Assessment International Education''' ('''CAIE''' or simply '''Cambridge''', formerly known as '''CIE''' - (University of) '''C'''ambridge '''I'''nternational '''E'''xaminations) is a provider of international qualifications, offering examinations and qualifications to 10,000 schools in more than 160 countries.<ref>{{cite web|title=Cambridge: About|url=http://www.cambridgeinternational.org/about-us/who-we-are/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Cambridge Assessment – Portrait|url=http://www.cambridgeassessment.org.uk/about-us/our-exam-boards/cambridge-international/}}</ref>
The board of education is a division of [[Cambridge Assessment]], the trading name of the University of Cambridge Local Examinations Syndicate (UCLES), founded in 1858<ref>{{cite web|title=Cambridge Assessment – Who we are|url=http://www.cambridgeassessment.org.uk/about-us/who-we-are/our-heritage/}}</ref> as a [[nonprofit organization|not-for-profit]] non-teaching department of the [[University of Cambridge]].<ref name="cambridge-news.co.uk">{{cite web|url=http://www.cambridge-news.co.uk/Inside-secret-location-thats-home-8-million-exam-papers/story-22364275-detail/story.html|title=Inside the secret location that’s home to 8 million exam papers|publisher=Cambridge News|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923224340/http://www.cambridge-news.co.uk/Inside-secret-location-thats-home-8-million-exam-papers/story-22364275-detail/story.html|archivedate=2015-09-23|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cambridgeassessment.org.uk/about-us/who-we-are/|title=Who we are|publisher=Cambridge Assessment}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cambridgeassessment.org.uk/about-us/our-exam-boards/ |title=Our exam boards |publisher=Cambridge Assessment |date= |accessdate=2014-08-26}}</ref>
==Qualifications== Cambridge offers primarily school-leaving qualifications for university entrance such as the Cambridge International General Certificate of Education – Advanced Level (Cambridge International GCE A-Levels).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cambridgeinternational.org/programmes-and-qualifications/cambridge-advanced/cambridge-international-as-and-a-levels/ |title=Cambridge International A-Levels |publisher=Cambridge |date= |accessdate=2017-10-04}}</ref> In addition, Cambridge provides Key Stage examinations for primary and secondary schools internationally.<ref>{{cite web|title=Cambridge International Programmes and Qualifications|url=http://www.cambridgeinternational.org/programmes-and-qualifications/}}</ref>
==Recognition== Cambridge qualifications are recognised for admission by UK [[universities]] (including [[Oxford]] and [[Cambridge]]) as well as universities in the [[United States]] ([[Stanford]] and all [[Ivy League]] universities), [[Canada]], [[European Union]], [[Middle East]], [[West Asia]], [[New Zealand]], [[India]], [[Pakistan]], [[Bangladesh]], [[Sri Lanka]], [[Nepal]] as well as in other countries.<ref name=CIERec>{{cite web|title=Cambridge International Programmes – Recognition|url=http://www.cambridgeinternational.org/programmes-and-qualifications/recognition-and-acceptance/}}</ref>
