{{Infobox writer |name = Joanna Klink |image = }}
'''Joanna Klink''' is an American poet. She was born in [[Iowa City, Iowa]]. She received an M.F.A. in Poetry from the [[Iowa Writers' Workshop]] and a Ph.D. in Humanities from [[Johns Hopkins University]]. She has been a member of the poetry faculty at [[The University of Montana]] since the fall of 2001.<ref>[http://hs.umt.edu/creativewriting/people/core-faculty.php University of Montana Creative Writing Program Faculty]</ref> Her most recent book is ''Excerpts from a Secret Prophecy'' ([[Penguin Books]], 2015).
==Publications== * ''They Are Sleeping'' ([[University of Georgia Press]], 2000) * ''Circadian'' (Penguin Books, 2007) * ''Raptus'' (Penguin Books, 2010) * ''Excerpts from a Secret Prophecy'' (Penguin Books, 2015)
==Honors and awards== * [[Rona Jaffe Foundation Writers' Award]] (2003) <ref>[http://www.ronajaffefoundation.org/past_recipients.html Rona Jaffe Foundation Writers' Awards > Past Recipients]</ref> * Briggs-Copeland Poet, Harvard University (2008-2011) * Jeannette Haien Ballard Writer's Award (2012) * Civitella Ranieri (2012) * American Academy of Arts and Letters (2013) * Amy Lowell Poetry Traveling Scholarship (2017-2018) * The Bogliasco Foundation (2018)
==External links== * [http://www.joannaklink.com/ Official website] * [http://www.penguin.com/author/joanna-klink/236683 Penguin Author Page]
